I donĺt believe it was the war that divided this nation as you mentioned above as much as it was the destruction that came from within our borders that piggy backed on the social unrest our nation was experiencing at that time. Had we stuck it out and invaded Hanoi, the war would have been one of our greatest trump and a great example of true democracy to the nations of the world. I have heard many Vietnamese who have said, they hoped that we would have invaded Hanoi, this is both North and South Vietnamese. But that wasnĺt in the game we were destined to play. We must now deal with the effects of those who failed us at home. I believe you when you say, that you would have been there to welcome us home if you had to do it all again. There are a lot of things many of us would do differently. But its today that counts as Ed has mentioned. <br><br>
